iles (2005) Environ. Sci. Technol., 39, pp. 9750-9758; Huo, H., Wang, M., Bloyd, C., Putsche, V., Life-cycle assessment of energy use and greenhouse gas emissions of soybean-derived biodiesel and renewable fuels (2009) Environ. Sci. Technol., 43, pp. 750-756; Lam, M.K., Lee, K.T., Mohamed, A.R., Life cycle assessment for the production of biodiesel: A case study in Malaysia for palm oil versus Jatropha oil (2009) Biofuels, Bioprod. Biorefin., 3, pp. 601-612; Papong, S., Chom-In, T., Noksa-Nga, S., Malakul, P., Life cycle energy efficiency and potentials of biodiesel production from palm oil in Thailand (2010) Energy Policy, 101, pp. 112-S118; Lardon, L., Helias, A., Sialve, B., Steyer, J.-P., Bernard, O., Life-cycle assessment of biodiesel production from microalgae (2009) Environ. Sci. Technol., 43, pp. 6475-6481; Achten, W.M.J., Mathijs, E., Muys, B., Proposing a life cycle land use impact calculation methodology (2009) Proceedings of the 6th International Conference on LCA in the Agri-Food Sector - Towards A Sustainable Management of the Food Chain, pp. 22-33. , Zurich, Switzerland, Nemecek, T.; Gaillard, G., Eds. Agroscope Reckenholz-Tänikon Research Station: Zurich, Switzerland; Lindeijer, E., Biodiversity and life support impacts of land use in LCA (2000) J. Cleaner Prod., 8, pp. 131-319; Köllner, T., Species-pool effect potentials (SPEP) as a yardstick to evaluate land use impacts on biodiversity (2000) J. Cleaner Prod., 8, pp. 293-311; Milà, I., Canals, L., Romanya, J., Cowell, S.J., Method for assessing impacts on life support functions (LSF) related to the use of fertile land in life cycle assessment (LCA) (2007) J. Cleaner Prod., 15, pp. 1426-1440; Maes, W.H., Heuvelmans, G., Muys, B., Assessment of land use impact on water-related ecosystem services capturing the integrated terrestrial-aquatic system (2009) Environ. Sci. Technol., 43, pp. 7324-7330; Garcia-Quijano, J.F., Peters, J., Cockx, L., Van Wyk, G., Rosanov, A., Deckmyn, G., Ceulemans, R., Muys, B